node.statement: CASE 1a-i: Assume g_3(B) = B. APPLICATION OF LEMMA 11.2: Since g_3(B) = B and B intersects supp(g_3) (specifically {2,3,5,6} is in both), by Lemma 11.2 we conclude supp(g_3) = {2, 3, 5, 6, c_1, ..., c_m} is entirely contained in B. EXPLICIT CONTENTS: B now contains {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, a_1, ..., a_n, b_1, ..., b_k, c_1, ..., c_m} = Omega. CONCLUSION: |B| = N = |Omega|. CONTRADICTION: This contradicts that B is non-trivial (requires |B| < N).
